    "# Session 03c — image-only pia surface with onset-feature scoring\n",
    "\n",
    "**Date.**  2026-04-19\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goal.**  Close the one remaining image-only pia failure (755252, autofluorescence-limited) by extracting intensity features at the N22 \"truth\" surface and building a classifier / selection rule that uses them.  Constraint: the final rule must run on the image alone — centroid data is for validation only.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Starting point.**  The v2.1 image-based estimator in `03_image_based_surface.py` matched N22 on 5/6 HCR subjects; on 755252 it landed in a thick autofluorescence sheet ~200 µm above the real pia, producing onset = 62.5 µm (target ≤ 10 µm).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Endpoint.**  New public API (`score_surface_quality`, `auto_select_surface` in `03_image_based_surface.py`; convenience wrapper `estimate_pia_surface_image_autoselect` in `benchmark_analysis.py`) matches N22 onset quality on **all 6** HCR subjects including 755252.  The fix is a *selection* over a small candidate bank, not a new fitter.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## The 4-iteration arc\n",
    "\n",
    "| # | question | result | artefact |\n",
    "|---|---|---|---|\n",
    "| 1 | Can a per-column intensity feature at z = N22 separate true pia from v2.1's AF-surface on 755252? | Yes — `below_near` (mean intensity in a 40 µm slab below z) is **0.052 at N22 vs 0.000 at v2.1** on 755252, cleanly distinguishing the two; 5× to 50× smaller gap on clean subjects. | `iterations/iter01_*` |\n",
    "| 2 | Can we use `below_near` to filter per-column tops *inside* v2.1's Stage-3 so the fitter avoids AF-contaminated tops? | **No** — per-top `below_near` is not separable between AF tops and pia tops.  The iter-1 signal came from evaluating the feature at the fitted *surface z*, not at individual tops.  Per-top filtering is a dead end. | `iterations/iter02_*` |\n",
    "| 3 | Can we score **whole candidate surfaces** (different channel subsets × `target_quantile`) by `below_near` and pick the best? | Almost — raw Q selects the 755252 fix correctly, but fails on 767018 where a surface deep inside tissue body has even higher `below_near`.  Fix: add a contrast term `Qcon_n = median((below-above)/(below+above+ε))` that is ≈ 1 at pia, ≈ 0 in the AF-to-pia gap, and 0.1–0.55 deep in tissue.  Rule `argmax Q s.t. Qcon_n ≥ 0.9` picks a valid pia candidate on **all 6** subjects. | `iterations/iter03_*` |\n",
    "| 4 | Does the selection rule work via the proper API (not inline scripting)? | Yes — added `score_surface_quality` + `auto_select_surface` to the image module and `estimate_pia_surface_image_autoselect` to the benchmark API.  Re-ran on all 6 subjects and selections match iter-3 exactly. | `iterations/iter04_*` |"
   ]
  },
