    "## Headline figure — the Q / Qcon_n plane\n",
    "\n",
    "Every dot is one fitted candidate surface (54 total = 6 subjects × 9 candidates including N22 and v2.1-default).  Color = centroid-based onset depth (lower = pia).  The contrast metric on the y-axis cleanly separates three physical regimes:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Top, y ≈ 1** — real-pia candidates.  High Q, below-surface tissue is bright while above-surface is dark PBS.\n",
    "- **Bottom-left, y ≈ 0** — gap / AF-top candidates.  `load_hcr_combined`'s clip-to-median floors both below and above to 0.\n",
    "- **Middle, y ∈ 0.1–0.55** — tissue-body false positives.  Surface is pushed ~100 µm deep so below *and* above both contain bright signal (AF, cells, neuropil).\n",
    "\n",
    "The dashed line is the 0.9 rejection threshold; `argmax Q` is applied to survivors.  Every N22 ground-truth surface (red circles) sits at Qcon_n ≈ 1, confirming the contrast metric aligns with centroid-truth."
   ]
